---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy — Latent the Ritual"
  description="What little Latent collects, and why. We ask for as little as possible and never sell your information."
>
  <main class="legal">
    <div class="legal-label">Privacy</div>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated 29 May 2026</p>

    <p>Latent is made by one person — Habib Saleh, in Joun, Lebanon. This policy explains what little we collect and why. The short version: we ask for as little as possible, we don't track you, and we never sell your information.</p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>The only thing we ever ask for is your email address, and only if you choose to subscribe to our newsletter. If you write to us, we also receive your message and your email address. That is all. This website uses no analytics, no advertising, and no tracking cookies.</p>

    <h2>The newsletter</h2>
    <p>If you subscribe, your email address is stored and managed by Buttondown, our email provider, and used only to send occasional updates about Latent. Every email includes an unsubscribe link, and you can leave at any time.</p>

    <h2>Your photographs</h2>
    <p>Latent is a darkroom, not a cloud service. The app develops your photographs on your own device, and we never receive, store, or have any access to them. If you keep your photos in iCloud or save your library to iCloud Drive, that syncing runs through your own Apple account — under your control, not ours.</p>

    <h2>Payments</h2>
    <p>Purchases and subscriptions are handled entirely by Apple through the App Store. We never see or receive your payment details.</p>

    <h2>The services we rely on</h2>
    <p>We keep our tools few: Buttondown for the newsletter, Apple for the App Store and payments, and Cloudflare for website hosting and our domain. Each maintains its own privacy practices.</p>

    <h2>Your choices</h2>
    <p>You can unsubscribe at any time, and you can ask us to delete anything we hold about you by writing to <a href="mailto:contact@latentritual.com">contact@latentritual.com</a>. Depending on where you live — for example the EU, the UK, or California — you may have additional rights over your data, and we will honor them.</p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>Latent is not directed at children, and we do not knowingly collect information from anyone under 16.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>If this policy changes, we will update this page and the date above.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about privacy? Email <a href="mailto:contact@latentritual.com">contact@latentritual.com</a>.</p>

    <a class="legal-back" href="/">← Latent the Ritual</a>
  </main>

  <style>
    .legal { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 140px 24px 120px; }
    .legal-label { font-family: var(--font-label); font-weight: 300; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.28em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--amber-dim); margin-bottom: 20px; }
    .legal h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 300; font-size: 40px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--text-bright); margin-bottom: 12px; }
    .legal-updated { font-family: var(--font-body); font-style: italic; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-ghost); margin-bottom: 48px; }
    .legal h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 400; font-size: 21px; color: var(--text-bright); margin: 40px 0 12px; }
    .legal p { font-family: var(--font-body); font-weight: 300; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .legal a { color: var(--amber); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light); }
    .legal a:hover { color: var(--text-bright); }
    .legal-back { display: inline-block; margin-top: 48px; font-family: var(--font-label); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--amber-dim); border-bottom: none; }
    .legal-back:hover { color: var(--text-bright); }
  </style>
</Base>
